I am pleased to get this opportunity to speak to all of ye about an issue very dear to me.  As many of ye may know, the gods have decreed that all guilds with fewer than 10 members will be disbanded... and the gods have indicated that this will be actively policed every month or so.  <br>
<br>
My leader, Lord Incubis, has asked me to speak on behalf of all Foxglove (who all had a heart-to-heart talk about these matters.)  We are a small close-knit guild, around 8 active members, mostly in the 40-50 range.  Our numbers have dwindled such that we can no longer put together guild raids or even groups, one of the main principles upon which our guild was founded.<br>
<br>
I know we are not the only guild facing these problems.  Two of the suggestions that have been brought before us are: Joining a larger guild and banding together a number of small guilds.<br>
<br>
If any guilds would be interested in consolidating forces or wish to find out more, you can learn more about Foxglove at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://members.aol.com/incubis%20rush/foxglove.htm">members.aol.com/incubis%2...xglove.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->  and/or email me at anna@cheerful.com or post them here.  I am an avid lurker upon these boards-- I usually check them daily.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your time and I encourage you to discuss this with your guildmates.  I will try to answer any questions you may have.  <br>
<br>
We'd like to find a home... a new home... of friends we can fight beside.  We love quests and guild raids.<br>
<br>
 <p>Aella Silverymoon<br>
High Priestess of Tunare,<br>
Anonymous Until I Reach 49, the Golden Level!<br>
