<br>
However, as we are stuck with their prononuncements, I will say this. Being absorbed by another guild or merging one or more guilds is a risky proposition. My biggest caution would be that all sides of the guilds that are merging do their homework. Read forum postings about the guild you are absorbing or merging with, read charters, hunt and socialize with them. Small, subtle differences in guild focus, mission and personality can have huge consequences, causing situations which create acrimony and ill will. <br>
<br>
Even in small, close-knit groups, such subtle differences can erupt into huge disagreements that can tear guilds apart. When bringing together two guilds of slightly different philosophies can be even worse. For my own guild, we usually advise against merging with another guild, simply because of this. We try to look more at the individuals in the guild, and see who among them we know would fit in with us, and who wouldn't. There are a number of fine guilds out there, and even among some of the best, there are people that we don't feel would fit with our way of thinking. <br>
<br>
All I advise is caution. I hope that Foxglove can survive in some form, either as their own guild, or as a part of something larger.<br>
